{
  "Artificial Intelligence": "Artificial Intelligence (AI) refers to the development of computer systems that can perform activities typically associated with human intelligence. These activities include understanding language, making decisions, recognizing speech, identifying images, solving problems, and learning from experience. AI technologies such as machine learning, deep learning, natural language processing, and computer vision are widely used in education, healthcare, smart assistants, business analytics, robotics, and automated systems.",

  "Machine Learning": "Machine Learning is a specialized field within Artificial Intelligence that allows systems to automatically learn patterns from data and improve their predictions over time without direct programming for every task. Common approaches include supervised learning, unsupervised learning, and reinforcement learning. Machine learning applications include recommendation engines, predictive maintenance, spam filtering, medical diagnosis, speech processing, and customer behavior analysis.",

  "Cloud Computing": "Cloud Computing enables users to access computing resources such as servers, storage, databases, networking services, and software applications through the internet rather than relying solely on local machines. It offers advantages including scalability, high availability, flexibility, and reduced infrastructure costs. Popular cloud platforms include Amazon Web Services (AWS), Microsoft Azure, and Google Cloud Platform (GCP), which support modern application deployment and data management.",

  "Data Science": "Data Science is the discipline of extracting useful information and insights from large volumes of data using statistical methods, programming, and machine learning techniques. It involves stages such as data acquisition, preprocessing, analysis, visualization, model development, and result interpretation. Data science solutions are commonly used in healthcare analytics, market forecasting, financial services, manufacturing optimization, and intelligent decision support systems."
